# Generated output under packages/site that is git-ignored but NOT prettier-ignored.
#
# Prettier does not read nested .gitignore files — only the root .gitignore and this file. So
# `packages/site/.gitignore` listing `.astro/`, `test-results/` and `playwright-report/` keeps them
# out of git but does nothing for `format:check`, which happily checks and rejects them.
#
# They only exist after `astro build` / `astro dev` or a Playwright run, and CI runs `format:check`
# BEFORE `npm run build` — so CI has been passing by accident of step ordering while any local run
# after a build was red. Listing them here fixes the local signal and removes that dependence on
# ordering.
packages/site/.astro/
packages/site/test-results/
packages/site/playwright-report/
